#!N  #!Rall11 Size Control #!N #!EC #!N #!N To change the 
size of an image, simply change the size of the Image 
window. Holding down the  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   left #!EF mouse button: #!N #!I0 
#!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N o Drag a horizontal border 
to shrink or expand the window vertically. #!N #!I30 #!N o 
Drag a vertical border to shrink or expand the window horizontally. 
#!N #!I30 #!N o Drag a corner to shrink or expand 
a window vertically  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   and #!EF horizontally. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF 
#!N #!N #!N #!I0 #!N Notes: #!N #!I30 #!N 1.  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Reset #!EF in the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Options #!EF pull-down menu restores the 
original  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   view #!EF of the object but not the original 
size of the window. #!N #!I30 #!N 2. If your visual 
program uses the Display rather than the Image tool, the image 
size can be changed only by changing the resolution parameter of 
Camera or AutoCamera (see  #!Lcamera,dxall780 h Camera  #!EL  and  #!Lautocam,dxall771 h AutoCamera  #!EL  in IBM Visualization Data 
Explorer User's Reference for descriptions of these tools.) #!I0 #!N #!N 
